## Guardrails
- Always model fees in backtests — never report gross P&L as the headline number
- Break-even win rate after fees is the minimum acceptable signal quality threshold
- If fees consume > 30% of gross P&L, the strategy edge is too thin — escalate to QR for review
- Verify Kalshi fee schedule quarterly — fees can change and invalidate existing models
- Slippage is also a cost — track actual fill vs expected fill price on every trade
